In article <1994Jan18.105511.28874@ringer.cs.utsa.edu> cbarkley@Alex.Engr.Trinity.Edu (The DarkMage) writes:
   The trouble with the one time pad is that it is cumbersome and inefficient.

The other trouble with one-time pads is that people often seem to
assume that a bunch of "random" numbers is really random,
even though they got them from a pseudo-random number generator
that's easily breakable, or use a random chunk from a dictionary,
or whatever.....

